<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">I don't think this necessarily suggests that enchanters/illusionists will no longer have illusions, because the few spells given so far are only teasers.  In the case of the wizards, I think it's supposed to be a true transformation, like the Human Torch or something.  Hmm, perhaps a hero whose battle cry is "flame on!" isn't the most appropriate to use as an example in an online forum.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, I would love to see illusions be more than appearance-altering party tricks with some benefits (factions, levitation, size, resistances, etc.) thrown in, but also projected illusions with high utility, like illusory enemies to distract mobs, doppleganger-type spells for lower levels, and so on.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
