<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">The problem I have with the *Illusionist* class (Qeynos-based 'good' enchanter) is that it is not balanced. Whether you call the spells 'illusions' or 'transformations' or anything else, the fact is the selection available to the *Illusionist* are the least interesting ones, and not the widest selection at that. They cannot cast illusions of those other classes' 'transformations,'  even. Illusionists do not get charms, nor do they get a full clarity buff line. When all that distinguishes them is the claim to illusions, that claim should be backed better than it is. I won't be rolling one to join my friends, who have decided to be Qeynos based... and that saddens me.
<br />

<br />
Lomeloth</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
